,Recommended,431600,32122894,Posted: 1 June,all,cosmicelegy,"It may be a repackage of rfactor, but I still find myself coming back to Automobilista over other similar racing sims time and time again. The cars included with Automobilista are top-notch, especially the assortment of F1 ""style"" cars from every major era of Formula 1. The included track list is lacking, but head over to Race Department and you'll find a wide assortment of high quality mods (Especially CART Extreme). The niche audience of this game has kept third part content at a high standard. The newly included Championship Creator is a long overdue addition that has added it to my sim racing schedule in the next few weeks, as well as the new Formula Ultimate car (2017 F1 ""Style"" Car).If you're getting into sim racing, this is one of my five ""must-have"" titles (the others being: iRacing, Assetto Corsa, rFactor 2, RaceRoom) and I would rate it third overall with a first place in physics/car handling and a second place in AI (after rF2)."
