ed F12016,  refunded - silly simcade physics and weird car handling.- Tried Nascar Heat Evolution, refunded - totally an arcade racer with a so called ""sim mode"" but does not have any form of realistic and believable handling  - nore do the cars actually stear more than100 degrees either direction (also, non linear steering appears to be build specifically with console players and gamepads in mind). Also - crap physics.- Rfactor2. Really pretty - really cool tyre model, plenty of content - but somehow is lacking in something special that I cant put my finger on.- Project Cars: <-- I wont touch this with a 10 ft pole.- Automobolista: Where the ♥♥♥♥ is the advertising for this sim, I should have discovered this ages ago, it's certainly a gem."
