,Recommended,431600,32580705,Posted: 19 June,all,acdcdave1387,"This is the single greatest exhibition of the original rFactor engine. The team at Reiza really outdid themselves here.The car selection is awesome. For fans of Formula 1 you have a car from almost every era. Open wheel fans in general can rejoice knowing that there is pretty much something from every level of professional racing. The other various types of vehicles provide a level of diversity that few other games have. The Brazilian stock cars are actually really cool, especially if you like touring cars.The track selection isn't the greatest. There is a large quantity of tracks and they are of high quality but the majority of them are smaller unknown Brazilian tracks. With that being said, most of them are really fun tracks though and there are always a LOT of different variations to each and every track.The audio, despite being this dated rFactor 1 engine, is well done. The engine recordings are spot on and the feel of the cars is terrific.The game is definitely one of the top sims out there. If you are a fan of proper sim racing then this is a title you must NOT pass up. If you are new to sim racing then this will still be a great title because you can always lower the realism and work your way up.The AI is fantastic by the way. Do yourself a favor and give this one a try folks."
