76561198163373966,Recommended,431600,30152205,Posted: 24 February,all,howsthecat,"Try the 1975 F1 car, called 'Formula Retro'.Try the 'Test day'.Pick you car and pick 'Johannesburg' as your track. This was the old Kyalami race circuit.Remove the 'Electronic aids' listed in the garage, and do so again in the 'Options' menu.Reduce the tyre pressures to 17.8 for the front, and 18.3 for the rear.Alter the camber to '0'.Now go and drive...Remember, the tyres are cold for the first lap, so don't push too hard yet.Hopefully you'll be getting a 'feel' for the car, and it should bring a smile to your face...After a while, you may feel confident enough to post a time on the 'Time trial', and you'll soon realise how much you want to do better...  ...and you get another go in 1m 13 seconds or so! Exhilarating isn't the word!Once I'd realised where all the 'Electronic aids' were in the menus, and removed them, I began to live.Even some time in the tardy Formula Vee helped my understanding of weight transfer.It's easy to over drive the car, and you need to control yourself to get the best out of it.And then there's the circuits...OLD Interlagos, with its fearsome double-apex first corner. I was taking the first part at 163mph! It takes your breath away.At Brasilia you'll begin to learn how to deal with the lack of grip. At Cascavel you'll have yor breath taken away again.The first corner is a full 180 degrees in fifth gear, ultimately leading into a VERY fast 4th gear left hander before you have to anchor it for a slow right. It's awesome!At Kansai, which is in fact Suzuka, you will be seriously challenged by the lack of grip. It's literally rally-driving a F1 car!Imagine taking a car like this to Britain's Cadwell park? It's a motorcycle track after all.Imagine no longer! Hanging on to this car at Cadwell requires your bravery as well as your judgement.Then you watch the replay and think, ""Wow, this is also fantastic to watch!""Having played 'Grand Prix Legends' in the past, now being able to drive the Brabham is fantastic, nothing less.My frustrations are with the dreaded 'understeer' on everything, but it's easily controllable on the Brabham 'Formula retro', but I'm trying to engineer it out, which is quite a challenge.Having learned some set-up lessons from the Formula Retro, hopefully I can apply them to the other cars should I choose to try them.The graphics are fine by me, and anyway, it's the feel of the car that matters.I use a cheap Thrustmaster (Non-force feedback) steering wheel, which works very well.I'm really pleased with this game.It's frustrating but very rewarding trying really hard to get the best out of that old Brabham."
