76561198157256457,Recommended,431600,24841620,"Posted: 12 August, 2016",all,Hawk,"As everyone else is saying: the ffb and physics on this game are THE NEXT LEVEL. Combined with the force feedback and handling of the cars is the sense of speed delivered in the way you're virtual head moves about inside the cockpit. I set the head motion and yaw exaggeration to the maximum, cranked up ""look ahead"" all the way, and it REALLY adds to the sense of g forces involved in cornering, accelerating and braking inside the cockpit as it feels like the car is violently bucking and surging, as it should in an F1 car.As far as graphics go I was about to delete the game from my system and go on a forum and ♥♥♥♥♥ about how crappy they are until I discovered that you have to DISABLE SweetFX in the initial setup screen of the game, keep Anti Aliasing OFF...and then go into the nvidia control panel and manually setup the Anti Aliasing there to OVERRIDE the game's settings.I bumped my Anti Aliasing up to 32 supersample and now the graphics are smooth as silk. If you just install the game as is with sweetFX enabled the graphics look a bit like playstation 1, so don't delete it from you system until you follow the above.Don't expect Assetto Corsa level graphics here but to me, it's all about the smoothness of the jaggies. The textures of the track are done quite nicely and are very detailed. The cars are modeled very well but there are a few bugs in some views, such as when looking to the rear while in the cockpit your back wheels won't be visible in the F1 car. But this is still pre launch so I'm sure it will get fixed. The terrain in general is a bit bland but on par.The thing I'm finding with the tracks is they are all a little bland just by their nature, but a blast to drive. So again, this sim isn't about showcasing eye candy, its about the EXPERIENCE, and in my opinion this is THE game for F1 hot lapping.I have not yet tried driving against the Ai so I can't speak about that, but my hunch is it will be intense. I've never had a game pull me so much into the feeling of driving an F1 car at high speed as this one. Just be sure to widen your field of view a bit back to get that sense of speed necessary.If you crave a pure F1 experience THIS is THE game."
